My favourite rainbows are not made of paint. They are made of magic.

When the sun shines over the hills, the sky turns blue. But sometimes, the clouds get very fluffy. They cover the whole sky like a big white blanket. The sun tries to come out, but it is hidden.

Then, the clouds start to move. They drift slowly across the sky. As they pass, they leave behind a trail of light. It looks like a bridge made of gold and pink. It looks like a rainbow.

I love these rainbows because they show that even when the sky is cloudy, there is still a beautiful place to look. They remind me that life is full of surprises. Sometimes, the best things happen when you wait for the clouds to move.

So, I look up at the sky. I wait for the next rainbow. I know I will find one soon. [end of text]


